1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,415
Welcome to the Self Leadership Mastery
Practice.

2
00:00:02,415 --> 00:00:06,399
This practice is about learning to lead
your inner system with steadiness,

3
00:00:06,399 --> 00:00:07,709
respect, and compassion.

4
00:00:07,709 --> 00:00:11,743
Self leadership does not mean controlling
your parts. It means listening from

5
00:00:11,743 --> 00:00:15,511
enough spaciousness that your parts do
not have to take over completely.

6
00:00:15,511 --> 00:00:17,229
Begin by settling your body.

7
00:00:17,229 --> 00:00:18,529
Let your shoulders soften.

8
00:00:18,529 --> 00:00:19,783
Let your jaw loosen.

9
00:00:19,783 --> 00:00:22,569
Let your breath be natural.

10
00:00:31,569 --> 00:00:31,569
<break time="3s" />

11
00:00:31,569 --> 00:00:32,962
Take a slow breath in.

12
00:00:41,962 --> 00:00:41,962
<break time="3s" />

13
00:00:41,962 --> 00:00:43,123
And let it out.

14
00:00:43,123 --> 00:00:46,142
Now bring to mind a recent moment when a
part of you felt activated.

15
00:00:46,142 --> 00:00:51,206
Choose something manageable. Not the
hardest thing. Just a moment when a part

16
00:00:51,206 --> 00:00:55,337
took over, reacted, withdrew, criticized,
protected, or pushed.

17
00:00:55,337 --> 00:00:56,684
Notice the scene gently.

18
00:00:56,684 --> 00:00:59,610
Where were you? What happened? What part
showed up?

19
00:01:11,610 --> 00:01:11,610
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

20
00:01:11,610 --> 00:01:12,678
Now pause the scene.

21
00:01:12,678 --> 00:01:14,907
Imagine you are watching it from a little
distance.

22
00:01:26,907 --> 00:01:26,907
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

23
00:01:26,907 --> 00:01:30,297
Ask: Which part of me was leading in that
moment?

24
00:01:42,297 --> 00:01:42,297
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:01:42,297 --> 00:01:46,807
Maybe a manager. Maybe a firefighter.
Maybe an inner critic. Maybe a people

26
00:01:46,807 --> 00:01:51,074
pleaser. Maybe an avoidant part. Maybe a
protector that wanted control.

27
00:01:51,074 --> 00:01:53,257
Notice that part without judging it.

28
00:01:53,257 --> 00:01:57,483
Now ask: What was this part trying to
accomplish?

29
00:02:09,483 --> 00:02:09,483
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

30
00:02:09,483 --> 00:02:10,923
What was it protecting?

31
00:02:22,923 --> 00:02:22,923
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

32
00:02:22,923 --> 00:02:24,734
What was it afraid would happen?

33
00:02:36,734 --> 00:02:36,734
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

34
00:02:36,734 --> 00:02:37,291
Listen.

35
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:55,291
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

36
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:58,217
Now ask: How do I feel toward this part
right now?

37
00:03:10,217 --> 00:03:10,217
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

38
00:03:10,217 --> 00:03:13,979
If you feel frustrated or ashamed, notice
that another part may be present.

39
00:03:13,979 --> 00:03:16,765
Ask that part for a little space too.

40
00:03:28,765 --> 00:03:28,765
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

41
00:03:28,765 --> 00:03:31,273
Self leadership begins with noticing who
is leading.

42
00:03:31,273 --> 00:03:34,524
Now imagine stepping into the scene with
more Self-energy.

43
00:03:46,524 --> 00:03:46,524
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

44
00:03:46,524 --> 00:03:49,450
You do not erase the part. You stand near
it.

45
00:03:49,450 --> 00:03:53,934
You might say to the part: I see that you
were trying to help. I understand that

46
00:03:53,934 --> 00:03:58,304
you felt something was at stake. I am
here now. You do not have to handle this

47
00:03:58,304 --> 00:03:58,645
alone.

48
00:04:07,645 --> 00:04:07,645
<break time="3s" />

49
00:04:07,645 --> 00:04:12,115
Now ask the part: What would you need
from me in order to let me lead a little

50
00:04:12,115 --> 00:04:12,986
more next time?

51
00:04:24,986 --> 00:04:24,986
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

52
00:04:24,986 --> 00:04:29,331
Maybe it needs reassurance, a plan,
protection, a boundary, a slower pace,

53
00:04:29,331 --> 00:04:31,116
more support, or more honesty.

54
00:04:31,116 --> 00:04:35,435
Now imagine the same situation again, but
this time Self is present.

55
00:04:47,435 --> 00:04:47,435
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

56
00:04:47,435 --> 00:04:48,596
Notice what changes.

57
00:04:48,596 --> 00:04:53,237
Maybe your body feels different. Maybe
your tone changes. Maybe you pause before

58
00:04:53,237 --> 00:04:57,349
responding. Maybe you name what is
happening. Maybe you set a boundary.

59
00:04:57,349 --> 00:05:00,345
Maybe you ask for time. Maybe you do
less, not more.

60
00:05:00,345 --> 00:05:02,621
Let the new possibility be simple.

61
00:05:02,621 --> 00:05:07,153
Now ask your system: What is one
leadership phrase I can use when I notice

62
00:05:07,153 --> 00:05:08,333
a part taking over?

63
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:20,333
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

64
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:25,399
Examples might be: I see you. Let me be
with this. We can slow down. I can listen

65
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:30,085
without letting you run the whole system.
You do not have to do this alone.

66
00:05:30,085 --> 00:05:32,361
Choose one phrase that feels true.

67
00:05:32,361 --> 00:05:35,565
Now imagine using that phrase during the
next difficult moment.

68
00:05:47,565 --> 00:05:47,565
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

69
00:05:47,565 --> 00:05:51,227
Let your body feel what it would be like
to pause, breathe, and lead from

70
00:05:51,227 --> 00:05:51,837
Self-energy.

71
00:05:51,837 --> 00:05:54,205
Take a slow breath in.

72
00:06:03,205 --> 00:06:03,205
<break time="3s" />

73
00:06:03,205 --> 00:06:04,505
And let it out.

74
00:06:04,505 --> 00:06:06,084
Thank the parts that showed up.

75
00:06:06,084 --> 00:06:07,477
Thank the protectors.

76
00:06:07,477 --> 00:06:09,660
Thank the part of you that is learning to
lead.

77
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:12,075
When you are ready, return to the room.

78
00:06:21,075 --> 00:06:21,075
<break time="3s" />

